{"title": "Trumpet Major", "description": "Our heroine, Anne Garland, lives quietly in a rural community deep in the English countryside.  However, the arrival of several regiments preparing for an expected invasion brings colour and chaos to the county.  A graceful and charming young woman, Anne is pursued by three suitors: John Loveday, the trumpet-major in a British regiment, honest and loyal; his brother Robert, a merchant seaman and womaniser, and Festus Derriman, the cowardly son of the local squire. Set at the time of the Napoleonic wars, this is the author's only historical novel, and unusually for Hardy's books, some of the characters live happily ever after.  (Summary adapted from Wikipedia by Cori Samuel.)", "duration": 42507, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "92", "name": "Thomas Hardy"}], "coverArt": "https://www.archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt15/Trumpet-Major_1203.jpg", "copyright_year": "1880", "genres": ["Published 1800 -1900"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Cori Samuel"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Cori Samuel"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Karen Merline"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Chapter 00 - Preface", "readers": [572], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/trumpetmajor_0904_librivox/trumpetmajor_00_hardy_64kb.mp3", "duration": 254}, {"section": 1, "title": "Chapter 01 - What Was Seen From the Window Overlooking the Down", "readers": [572], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/trumpetmajor_0904_librivox/trumpetmajor_01_hardy_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1251}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter 02 - Somebody Knocks and Comes In", "readers": [572], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/trumpetmajor_0904_librivox/trumpetmajor_02_hardy_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1086}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter 03 - The Mill Becomes an Important Centre of Operations", "readers": [572], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/trumpetma